Use these pre-built chat-UI patterns. DO NOT invent bubble geometry — the snippets below handle long messages, multi-line input, and timestamps correctly.

**MESSAGE LIST CONTAINER** (auto-scroll to bottom on new message):
```html
<div id="messages" class="messages">
  <!-- bubbles inserted here -->
</div>
```
```css
.messages {
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  overflow-y: auto;
  padding: 16px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 8px;
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
}
```
```javascript
function scrollMessagesToBottom(container = document.getElementById('messages')) {
  // Use scrollHeight to bypass scroll-behavior:smooth on initial load if needed.
  container.scrollTop = container.scrollHeight;
}
```

**MESSAGE BUBBLE** (sent + received variants — handles wrap, max-width):
```html
<div class="msg msg-received">
  <img class="msg-avatar" src="..." alt="" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="msg-stack">
    <div class="msg-author">Alice</div>
    <div class="msg-bubble">
      Hello! How are you doing today?
    </div>
    <time class="msg-time">2:14 PM</time>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="msg msg-sent">
  <div class="msg-stack">
    <div class="msg-bubble">Doing great, thanks for asking!</div>
    <time class="msg-time">2:15 PM <span class="read-receipt">✓✓</span></time>
  </div>
</div>
```
```css
.msg {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
  align-items: flex-end;
  max-width: 100%;
}
.msg-received { align-self: flex-start; }
.msg-sent     { align-self: flex-end; flex-direction: row-reverse; }
.msg-avatar {
  width: 32px; height: 32px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  object-fit: cover;
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  background: var(--avatar-bg, #475569);
}
.msg-stack {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2px;
  max-width: min(72%, 480px); /* Prevents super-long bubbles on wide screens */
}
.msg-sent .msg-stack { align-items: flex-end; }
.msg-author {
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text-muted, #94a3b8);
  margin-bottom: 1px;
}
.msg-bubble {
  padding: 9px 14px;
  border-radius: 18px;
  background: var(--bubble-received, #334155);
  color: var(--text, #f1f5f9);
  word-wrap: break-word;
  overflow-wrap: anywhere; /* Wraps very long words/URLs without overflow */
  white-space: pre-wrap;   /* Preserves user line breaks */
  line-height: 1.4;
}
.msg-sent .msg-bubble {
  background: var(--bubble-sent, #3b82f6);
  color: #fff;
  /* Asymmetric corner: bottom-right square = 'tail' */
  border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;
}
.msg-received .msg-bubble {
  border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;
}
.msg-time {
  font-size: 10px;
  color: var(--text-muted, #94a3b8);
  margin-top: 2px;
}
.read-receipt { color: #22c55e; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 11px; }
.read-receipt.unread { color: var(--text-muted, #94a3b8); }
```

